{"id": "EUVD-2022-55697", "enisaUuid": "b54fac97-5ab4-3a0a-b421-b2b289bbe361", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nperf/x86/intel/uncore: Fix reference count leak in snr_uncore_mmio_map()\n\npci_get_device() will increase the reference count for the returned\npci_dev, so snr_uncore_get_mc_dev() will return a pci_dev with its\nreference count increased. We need to call pci_dev_put() to decrease the\nreference count. Let's add the missing pci_dev_put().", "datePublished": "2025-12-08T03:31:02", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-08T03:31:02", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/d2afced51108813256d8072c6e464b0c9f0bb890", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/433bd587dca5c3f7157fef2fe571290cd392cbf6", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a67146437b6428069b71a7e5e740a2a8e1c40ac9", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/dc7f07bc1ebb56a23fd1c4f664db5cbeb8900800", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8ebd16c11c346751b3944d708e6c181ed4746c39", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50615"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50615"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "1c8754dc-1219-38ce-9e4a-224c8ae27544", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "ee49532b38dd084650bf715eabe7e3828fb8d275 <433bd587dca5c3f7157fef2fe571290cd392cbf6"}, {"id": "2cf552d3-dbeb-3148-b552-0af1e4e5e2db", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.10.163"}, {"id": "32e0557b-104d-39f7-8ae7-22eee0288983", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "ee49532b38dd084650bf715eabe7e3828fb8d275 <d2afced51108813256d8072c6e464b0c9f0bb890"}, {"id": "3768177c-a9b5-37ec-8800-40d81e2385f9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "ee49532b38dd084650bf715eabe7e3828fb8d275 <8ebd16c11c346751b3944d708e6c181ed4746c39"}, {"id": "79e54c11-a82a-3086-a222-7c8b77d2cd48", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0.16"}, {"id": "7fecaa61-cb58-3aa6-b906-3dd591cb1217", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "produc